<p><rs type="material" key="marmor">White marble</rs> monumental <rs type="objectType">block</rs> with wide flat mouldings, from which some moulding has been chipped away to facilitate reuse (a: <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="width">0.93</measure>   × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.55</measure>   × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="depth">0.44</measure>) broken into five fragments, of which only one has been found again. The mouldings suggest that this could have served as a <rs type="objectType" cert="low">lintel</rs> over a doorway.</p></div><div type="description" n="text"><head>Description of Text</head><p>The text is cut on the broad upper moulding (ll. 1-7) and on a lower moulding (ll. 8-9).</p>
</div>
